{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862573608,"sessionID":"ses_2865b0a75ffepxYCm60X9v5r8p","part":{"id":"prt_d79a6e52f001PZfYSf0tKpMUK0","messageID":"msg_d79a6ce47001JCo4JicsCC2j82","sessionID":"ses_2865b0a75ffepxYCm60X9v5r8p","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","content":"# AR-011 Design: Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-011  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Medium\n\nThe JWT Manager provides secure, stateless authentication between the Router and sandbox pods using RSA-signed JWT tokens. It handles RSA key pair generation (2048-bit), RS256 token signing with configurable claims, and key persistence in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility and pod restart resilience.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           JWT Manager Component                              │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Key Generation │───▶│  Token Signing  │───▶│  Kubernetes Persistence │  │\n│  │  (RSA 2048)     │    │  (RS256)        │    │  (Secret Storage)       │  │\n│  └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────────────┘  │\n│           │                      │                       │                   │\n│           ▼                      ▼                       ▼                   │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │                       Router Server                                  │    │\n│  │  - Calls GenerateToken() for each proxied request                   │    │\n│  │  - Embeds session_id in JWT claims                                  │    │\n│  │  - Attaches Authorization: Bearer <token> header                    │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           Sandbox Pod                                        │\n│  - Validates JWT signature using public key                                  │\n│  - Extracts session_id from claims                                           │\n│  - Processes authenticated request                                           │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **JWTManager** | Manages RSA keys and JWT signing | Claims map (`session_id`, etc.) | Signed JWT string |\n| **RSA Key Generator** | Creates cryptographically secure key pairs | rand.Reader, 2048 bits | Private/Public key pair |\n| **Token Generator** | Builds and signs JWT claims | Base claims + custom claims | RS256-signed token |\n| **Secret Manager** | Persists keys in Kubernetes | PEM-encoded keys | K8s Secret CRUD |\n| **Router Server** | Uses JWT for request authentication | Session info | Proxied request with JWT |\n\n### Key Persistence Flow\n\n```\nServer Startup\n     │\n     ▼\nNewJWTManager()\n(generate RSA key pair)\n     │\n     ▼\nTryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()\n     │\n┌────┴─────────────────┐\n│                      │\nIn-cluster?         Not in-cluster\n│                      │\n▼                      ▼\nCreate/Load Secret   Log warning\n     │               Use ephemeral keys\n     ▼\nSecret 'picod-router-identity'\n├── private.pem (RSA PRIVATE KEY)\n└── public.pem  (PUBLIC KEY)\n```\n\n### Token Generation Flow\n\n```\nHTTP Request Received\n         │\n         ▼\nSession Resolved (via SessionManager)\n         │\n         ▼\nJWTManager.GenerateToken(claims)\n         │\n    ┌────┴────┐\n    ▼         ▼\nBase Claims   Custom Claims\n- exp         - session_id\n- iat         (from SessionInfo)\n- iss\n    │         │\n    └────┬────┘\n         ▼\nSign with RS256\n(private key)\n         │\n         ▼\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n(set on proxied request)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/router/\n├── jwt.go              # JWTManager implementation - RSA key gen, token signing, secret storage\n├── errors.go           # Error types including JWTSigningError\n├── config.go           # Configuration including IdentityNamespace\n└── ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### JWTManager\n\n```go\n// JWTManager handles JWT key generation and token signing.\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `privateKey` | `*rsa.PrivateKey` | RSA private key for RS256 signing |\n| `publicKey` | `*rsa.PublicKey` | RSA public key for signature verification |\n| `clientset` | `kubernetes.Interface` | Kubernetes client for Secret operations |\n\n### Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `rsaKeySize` | `2048` | RSA key bit length |\n| `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` | Default token validity duration |\n| `identitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` | Kubernetes Secret name for key storage |\n| `privateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` | Secret data key for private key |\n| `publicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` | Secret data key for public key |\n\n### Package Variables\n\n| Variable | Type | Default | Description |\n|----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `IdentityNamespace` | `string` | `\"default\"` | Namespace for JWT secret storage, set from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var |\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Constructor\n\n```go\n// NewJWTManager creates a new JWTManager with a generated RSA key pair.\nfunc NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Generates a new 2048-bit RSA key pair using cryptographically secure random source (`crypto/rand`)\n- Returns error with message \"failed to generate RSA key\" on failure\n- The `clientset` field is initially nil and set later by `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()`\n\n### Token Operations\n\n```go\n// GenerateToken creates a JWT with the given claims.\nfunc (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Creates base claims: `exp` (now + 5 minutes), `iat` (now), `iss` (\"agentcube-router\")\n- Merges custom claims (e.g., `session_id` from SessionInfo)\n- Custom `exp` in claims overrides default expiration\n- Signs with RS256 using the private key\n- Returns error with message \"failed to sign token\" on signing failure\n\n```go\n// GetPublicKeyPEM returns the public key in PKIX PEM format.\nfunc (m *JWTManager) GetPublicKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Encodes public key using `x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey`\n- Returns PEM block with type \"PUBLIC KEY\"\n- Returns error if marshaling fails\n\n```go\n// GetPrivateKeyPEM returns the private key in PKCS#1 PEM format.\nfunc (m *JWTManager) GetPrivateKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Encodes private key using `x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey`\n- Returns PEM block with type \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\"\n\n### Key Persistence Operations\n\n```go\n// TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret attempts to store keys in K8s secret or load existing.\nfunc (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret() error\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Attempts to get in-cluster Kubernetes config via `rest.InClusterConfig()`\n- If not in-cluster: logs warning and returns nil (uses ephemeral keys)\n- Creates clientset and attempts to create Secret\n- If Secret already exists: loads existing keys and replaces ephemeral keys\n- Returns descriptive errors for client creation or secret operation failures\n\n**Secret Specification:**\n- Name: `picod-router-identity`\n- Namespace: `IdentityNamespace` (from env var or \"default\")\n- Type: `Opaque`\n- Labels: `app=agentcube`, `component=router`\n- Data keys: `private.pem`, `public.pem`\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n#### JWTSigningError\n\n```go\n// JWTSigningError represents an error when JWT signing fails.\ntype JWTSigningError struct {\n    Cause error\n}\n\nfunc (e *JWTSigningError) Error() string\nfunc NewJWTSigningError(cause error) *JWTSigningError\n```\n\nUsed in router handlers when token generation fails.\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Error Message | Returned By |\n|----------|---------------|-------------|\n| RSA key generation failure | `failed to generate RSA key: %w` | `NewJWTManager()` |\n| Token signing failure | `failed to sign token: %w` | `GenerateToken()` |\n| Public key marshal failure | `failed to marshal public key: %w` | `GetPublicKeyPEM()` |\n| K8s client creation failure | `failed to create Kubernetes client: %w` | `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` |\n| Secret creation failure | `failed to create JWT secret: %w` | `createOrLoadSecret()` |\n| Existing secret retrieval failure | `failed to get existing JWT secret: %w` | `loadExistingSecret()` |\n| Missing private key in secret | `existing JWT secret missing private key data` | `loadExistingSecret()` |\n| PEM decode failure | `failed to decode PEM block` | `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` |\n| PKCS#1 parse failure | `failed to parse private key: %w` | `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` |\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Key Generation Errors**: Fatal on startup - returns error to caller\n2. **Token Signing Errors**: Returns wrapped error for handler to respond with 500\n3. **K8s Client Errors**: Returns error for in-cluster failures; logs warning for non-cluster\n4. **Secret Creation Errors**: Returns error except for `AlreadyExists` (triggers load)\n5. **Key Loading Errors**: Returns error for malformed secret data\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Component | Test Cases | Expected Behavior |\n|-----------|------------|-------------------|\n| `NewJWTManager` | RSA key generation | Returns valid JWTManager with 2048-bit keys |\n| `NewJWTManager` | Random source | Uses `crypto/rand` for secure generation |\n| `GenerateToken` | Valid claims | Returns valid RS256-signed JWT string |\n| `GenerateToken` | Standard claims | Includes exp, iat, iss automatically |\n| `GenerateToken` | Custom claims | Merges session_id and other custom claims |\n| `GenerateToken` | Custom expiration | Custom exp overrides default 5 minutes |\n| `GenerateToken` | Signing error | Returns error with \"failed to sign token\" |\n| `GetPublicKeyPEM` | Valid encoding | Returns PKIX PEM with \"PUBLIC KEY\" header |\n| `GetPrivateKeyPEM` | Valid encoding | Returns PKCS#1 PEM with \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\" header |\n| `GetPublicKeyPEM`/`GetPrivateKeyPEM` | PEM format | Returns valid UTF-8, parseable by PEM decoders |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Scenario | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Secret creation | Creates new Secret with correct labels and data |\n| Secret loading | Loads existing keys when Secret already exists |\n| Non-cluster mode | Returns nil error, logs warning for non-K8s environments |\n| Key persistence | Keys stored in Secret match generated keys |\n| Key retrieval | Loaded keys match previously stored keys |\n| Token validation | Generated tokens can be validated with stored public key |\n| Expired token | Tokens past exp claim fail validation |\n| Invalid signature | Tokens signed with different key fail validation |\n\n### Mock Dependencies\n\n- `kubernetes.Interface` for Secret operations\n- `crypto/rand.Reader` can use deterministic source for reproducible tests\n\n### Coverage Targets\n\n- Minimum: 80%\n- Target: 90%\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Direct Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT token creation and RS256 signing |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes client for Secret operations |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | v0.32.0 | Secret type definitions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | v0.32.0 | K8s API error handling (AlreadyExists) |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | v0.32.0 | ObjectMeta, CreateOptions, etc. |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/rest` | v0.32.0 | In-cluster config detection |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n\n### Standard Library\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `crypto/rand` | Cryptographically secure random number generation |\n| `crypto/rsa` | RSA key generation and signing |\n| `crypto/x509` | Key encoding/decoding (PKIX, PKCS#1) |\n| `encoding/pem` | PEM format encoding/decoding |\n| `fmt` | Error formatting |\n| `os` | Environment variable reading |\n| `time` | Token expiration timestamps |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace for JWT identity Secret |\n\n### Configuration Flow\n\n```go\nvar IdentityNamespace = \"default\"\n\nfunc init() {\n    if ns := os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"); ns != \"\" {\n        IdentityNamespace = ns\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### RSA Key Generation\n\n```go\nprivateKey, err := rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)\n```\n\n- Uses `crypto/rand.Reader` for secure random generation\n- 2048-bit key size provides balance of security and performance\n- Private key contains embedded public key\n\n### Token Claims Structure\n\n```json\n{\n    \"exp\": 1710000000,           // Expiration: now + 5 minutes\n    \"iat\": 1709999700,           // Issued at: current timestamp\n    \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",   // Issuer identifier\n    \"session_id\": \"sess-abc-123\" // Custom claim from SessionInfo\n}\n```\n\n### PEM Encoding\n\n**Private Key (PKCS#1):**\n```\n-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n<base64-encoded PKCS#1 data>\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n```\n\n**Public Key (PKIX):**\n```\n-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n<base64-encoded PKIX data>\n-----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Secret Structure\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Secret\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-router-identity\n  namespace: <AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE>\n  labels:\n    app: agentcube\n    component: router\ntype: Opaque\ndata:\n  private.pem: <base64-encoded PKCS#1 PEM>\n  public.pem: <base64-encoded PKIX PEM>\n```\n\n### Algorithm: RS256\n\n- **Signing**: RSA private key + SHA-256 hash\n- **Verification**: RSA public key + SHA-256 hash\n- **Key format**: PKCS#1 for private, PKIX for public\n- **Token format**: JWS Compact Serialization (header.payload.signature)\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Key Management\n\n1. **Private Key Protection**: Private key never leaves the Router pod or K8s Secret\n2. **Public Key Distribution**: Public key can be safely distributed to sandbox pods\n3. **Secret Access**: Requires RBAC permission to create/get Secrets in target namespace\n4. **Ephemeral Fallback**: Non-cluster environments use ephemeral keys (logged warning)\n\n### Token Security\n\n1. **Short-lived tokens**: 5-minute expiration limits exposure window\n2. **Unique signatures**: RS256 ensures tokens cannot be forged without private key\n3. **Session binding**: session_id claim ties token to specific session\n4. **No refresh tokens**: Short expiration, session-level lifecycle management\n\n### RBAC Requirements\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-router-jwt\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"secrets\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"get\"]\n  resourceNames: [\"picod-router-identity\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n### Adding JWT Support\n\n1. **New dependency**: Already included in go.mod (`github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`)\n2. **RBAC setup**: Ensure Router has Secret create/get permissions\n3. **Namespace configuration**: Set `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` for non-default namespace\n4. **Key rotation**: Delete `picod-router-identity` Secret to trigger new key generation\n\n### Downstream Changes\n\n- Sandbox pods must validate JWT using public key from Secret\n- Public key can be mounted as volume from Secret or fetched via K8s API\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager implementation with key generation, token signing, and secret storage |\n| `pkg/router/errors.go` | JWTSigningError and other error types |\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | IdentityNamespace configuration |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-009](changes/AR-009/design.md) — Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n- [AR-010](changes/AR-010/design.md) — Router Session Management\n- [Session Routing Design](../../session-routing/design.md) — Router design overview\n- [Client-Go Library](../../deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client usage\n- [JWT Specification](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519) — RFC 7519\n- [JWS Specification](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7515) — RFC 7515 (RS256)\n- [Delta Specification](delta-spec.md) — Detailed requirements and scenarios\n\n---\n\n*AR-011 — Module: pkg/router — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/errors.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":75,"character":53},"end":{"line":75,"character":64}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":87,"character":2},"end":{"line":87,"character":16}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#mapsloop"},"source":"mapsloop","message":"Replace m[k]=v loop with maps.Copy"},{"range":{"start":{"line":177,"character":65},"end":{"line":177,"character":68}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#SA1012"},"source":"SA1012","message":"do not pass a nil Context, even if a function permits it; pass context.TODO if you are unsure about which Context to use"},{"range":{"start":{"line":191,"character":68},"end":{"line":191,"character":71}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#SA1012"},"source":"SA1012","message":"do not pass a nil Context, even if a function permits it; pass context.TODO if you are unsure about which Context to use"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","time":{"start":1775862573578,"end":1775862573605}}}}
