{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862578594,"sessionID":"ses_2865b0a75ffepxYCm60X9v5r8p","part":{"id":"prt_d79a878eb001csQnwNkACiT4EO","messageID":"msg_d79a86a69001FAPVo6i7bifrLC","sessionID":"ses_2865b0a75ffepxYCm60X9v5r8p","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 Design: Router JWT 认证与签发\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-011  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Medium\n9: \n10: The JWT Manager provides secure, stateless authentication between the Router and sandbox pods using RSA-signed JWT tokens. It handles RSA key pair generation (2048-bit), RS256 token signing with configurable claims, and key persistence in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility and pod restart resilience.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                           JWT Manager Component                              │\n21: │                                                                              │\n22: │  ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐  │\n23: │  │  Key Generation │───▶│  Token Signing  │───▶│  Kubernetes Persistence │  │\n24: │  │  (RSA 2048)     │    │  (RS256)        │    │  (Secret Storage)       │  │\n25: │  └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────────────┘  │\n26: │           │                      │                       │                   │\n27: │           ▼                      ▼                       ▼                   │\n28: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n29: │  │                       Router Server                                  │    │\n30: │  │  - Calls GenerateToken() for each proxied request                   │    │\n31: │  │  - Embeds session_id in JWT claims                                  │    │\n32: │  │  - Attaches Authorization: Bearer <token> header                    │    │\n33: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n34: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n35:                                     │\n36:                                     ▼\n37: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n38: │                           Sandbox Pod                                        │\n39: │  - Validates JWT signature using public key                                  │\n40: │  - Extracts session_id from claims                                           │\n41: │  - Processes authenticated request                                           │\n42: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### Component Interactions\n46: \n47: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n48: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n49: | **JWTManager** | Manages RSA keys and JWT signing | Claims map (`session_id`, etc.) | Signed JWT string |\n50: | **RSA Key Generator** | Creates cryptographically secure key pairs | rand.Reader, 2048 bits | Private/Public key pair |\n51: | **Token Generator** | Builds and signs JWT claims | Base claims + custom claims | RS256-signed token |\n52: | **Secret Manager** | Persists keys in Kubernetes | PEM-encoded keys | K8s Secret CRUD |\n53: | **Router Server** | Uses JWT for request authentication | Session info | Proxied request with JWT |\n54: \n55: ### Key Persistence Flow\n56: \n57: ```\n58: Server Startup\n59:      │\n60:      ▼\n61: NewJWTManager()\n62: (generate RSA key pair)\n63:      │\n64:      ▼\n65: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()\n66:      │\n67: ┌────┴─────────────────┐\n68: │                      │\n69: In-cluster?         Not in-cluster\n70: │                      │\n71: ▼                      ▼\n72: Create/Load Secret   Log warning\n73:      │               Use ephemeral keys\n74:      ▼\n75: Secret 'picod-router-identity'\n76: ├── private.pem (RSA PRIVATE KEY)\n77: └── public.pem  (PUBLIC KEY)\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Token Generation Flow\n81: \n82: ```\n83: HTTP Request Received\n84:          │\n85:          ▼\n86: Session Resolved (via SessionManager)\n87:          │\n88:          ▼\n89: JWTManager.GenerateToken(claims)\n90:          │\n91:     ┌────┴────┐\n92:     ▼         ▼\n93: Base Claims   Custom Claims\n94: - exp         - session_id\n95: - iat         (from SessionInfo)\n96: - iss\n97:     │         │\n98:     └────┬────┘\n99:          ▼\n100: Sign with RS256\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 500. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 Design: Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-011  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Medium\n\nThe JWT Manager provides secure, stateless authentication between the Router and sandbox pods using RSA-signed JWT tokens. It handles RSA key pair generation (2048-bit), RS256 token signing with configurable claims, and key persistence in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility and pod restart resilience.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           JWT Manager Component                              │","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/design.md","time":{"start":1775862578582,"end":1775862578591}}}}
